</div> 
<p><strong>Serpent Bow</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Bows" href="/Bows" target="">Bow</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Serpent Bow</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a> and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for long ranged combat.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Malformed bow in the shape of a pair of poisonous snakes. Imbues arrows with poison through pagan magic, revealing its true worth when used with poison-infused arrows. <br>Used by assassins known as the Formless Serpents. </em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Serpent Bow in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Serpent Bow weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Serpent Bow can be found by a pool of rot in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Abandoned Cave" href="/Abandoned+Cave" target="">Abandoned Cave</a>. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=4152&amp;lat=-175.35&amp;lng=141.38&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=4152&amp;lat=-175.35&amp;lng=141.38&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Map here</a>]</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Serpent Bow Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon Skill: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Mighty Shot" href="/Mighty+Shot">Mighty Shot</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li><strong>Serpent Bow</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones<br></a></li> 
 <li>Adds a base of 15 poison build-up to all arrows. This leaves a visible effect on the arrows. 
  <ul> 
   <li>Best paired with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Serpent Arrow" href="/Serpent+Arrow">Serpent Arrows</a> for faster poisoning. Specially effective when using its skill, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Mighty Shot" href="/Mighty+Shot">Mighty Shot</a>.</li> 
   <li>The poison inflicted is not <strong>deadly poison</strong>, despite bearing similar design elements to the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Serpentbone Blade" href="/Serpentbone+Blade">Serpentbone Blade</a>&nbsp;and the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Venomous Fang" href="/Venomous+Fang">Venomous Fang</a>. See (<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Poison" href="/Poison">Poison</a>) for more information.&nbsp;</li> 
   <li>The buildup of Scarlet Rot from <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Rotbone Arrow" href="/Rotbone+Arrow">Rotbone Arrows</a> is not affected by this bow, since Scarlet Rot doesn't scale.</li> 
   <li>The way this bow works is adding poison build-up to all arrow-like fired projectiles, including crossbows. 
    <ul> 
     <li>This means all you have to do is hold this bow in one hand, and it will still add poison build-up to any projectiles fired from any bow or crossbow of your choice in the other hand. It will take&nbsp;more hits than just using the Serpent Bow itself, but if you hit enough times, it will proc poison.<br><br></li> 
    </ul> </li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>The Arcane scaling on this weapon does <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>not</strong></span>&nbsp;affect damage. The arcane scaling only affects the build-up of poison, bleed, and sleep passive effects of arrows. This bow is mostly advantageous with builds that integrate medium to high arcane. 
  <ul> 
   <li>Deals similar damage to the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Longbow" href="/Longbow">Longbow</a>, and shares the same Weapon Skill. Can be a potential substitute for it.</li> 
   <li>At low levels the Black Bow or any <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Light Bows" href="/Light+Bows">Light Bow</a> with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Barrage" href="/Barrage">Barrage</a> may be more effective for quickly applying status buildup (at short range).<br><br></li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;100.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Moveset &amp; Videos in&nbsp;Elden Ring for&nbsp;Serpent Bow</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Videos for the Serpent Bow Coming Soon</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Serpent Bow Upgrades in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a>&nbsp;page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></p> 
<p>This upgrade can't be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells" target="">Magic</a> nor boosted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</p> 
